name: The Streets Lit Up, 18"x12" on Fuji Crystal Archive Gloss
description: Shanghai thunderstorm, pictured in April 2012. 50% of all profit will go to XinXing Aid For Street Kids in China. XinXing is an independent, non-profit organization that was created in 2001 by a group of Médecins Sans Frontières staff. They help to rebuild the lives of abandoned and disadvantaged children, providing psychological intervention, medical aid, educational support and social investigation. The children are able to share their traumas, restore links with their families and rebuild their self-confidence in preparation for a proper return to society. Photograph © Alex Robertson http://www.alexrphotography.com
